<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-2071] RP.describeOwnership() does some bad math</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2071</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the input isn&apos;t sorted correctly for some reason, then describeOwnership() fails to calculate the ownership %ages correctly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Repro is 2 nodes with these tokens, you get these fractions:&lt;br/&gt;
49000620740128447720217646403197156812 : 0.7615167&lt;br/&gt;
770141183460469231731687303715884105727 : 4.2384834&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;423% ownership is obviously broken.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
